28/12/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Democratic Party (PD), one of the main partners in the coalition government, agreed on Wednesday (December 27th) to co-operate with the Liberal Democratic Party (PLD), which formed after defecting from PD's current cabinet partner, the National Liberal Party (PNL). 
The agreement was reached during a meeting between PD leader Emil Boc and PLD chairman Theodor Stolojan in Bucharest. 
According to statements after the talks, the parties have decided to work together in parliament to promote key legislative projects and to establish a stable right-wing base in the country. 
(Romania Libera, Nine o'clock - 28/12/06; Mediafax - 27/12/06)
